Strings in java is immutable because of a memory optimization using stringpool.
But we can make it mutable using StringBuffer class.


CODE:

package String;

public class StringBufferDemo {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
   
		StringBuffer str =  new StringBuffer("abc");
		str.setCharAt(0, 'h');
		System.out.println(str);
	}

}
